 existed in 1850, when the author was forced to abandon his work. Accompanying Moreau's transcription is an introductory essay and a textual introduction, extensive critical annotations, historical and modern maps, and a biographical appendix. The definitive collection of Thompson's works, The Writings of David Thompson will bring one of North American's most important early travellers and surveyors and his world to a whole new generation of readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aMoreau, William E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMoreau, William E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357723740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773577237423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773577237/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles